R' and one of R3 and R4 may be bonded to each other to form a bidentate ligand;
X1, X2 and X3 are anionic ligands as defined below;
L is a neutral electron donor; and
R3 and R4 together may form a fused aromatic ring system, i.e. a phenylindenylidene ligand, including salts, solvates and enantiomers thereof.

